00:23:43.530 --> 00:23:45.290
&gt;&gt; Jerry Pinkney: Do
I ever get frustrated

00:23:45.290 --> 00:23:49.040
when my drawing doesn't turn
the out way I want it to be?

00:23:49.040 --> 00:23:51.800
As a young artist you did
because you're always searching

00:23:51.800 --> 00:23:55.510
for an idea actually to build on.

00:23:55.510 --> 00:24:01.200 position:56%
I will tell you this, though, the
frustration as an adult artist tends

00:24:01.200 --> 00:24:04.390
to lead to a better result.

00:24:04.390 --> 00:24:09.420
Why? Because frustration means
that what you see that comes

00:24:09.420 --> 00:24:12.110
to mind first is not working.

00:24:12.110 --> 00:24:17.660
Most oftentimes in order
to do a more original idea,

00:24:17.660 --> 00:24:19.830
you have to dig a little deeper.

00:24:19.830 --> 00:24:24.200
And the gateway to sometimes
digging deeper is frustration,

00:24:24.200 --> 00:24:28.200
that something isn't work and
then how do I make it work?

00:24:28.200 --> 00:24:29.890
That's a very good question.

00:24:29.890 --> 00:24:31.190
Yes.

00:24:31.190 --> 00:24:32.490
[ Inaudible ]

00:24:32.490 --> 00:24:34.550
&gt;&gt; Jerry Pinkney: Oh thank
